## Bonus tip jo aapko viva mein bachayega

Ek aur cheez share kar deta hoon jo bahut students miss karte hain. Jab aap in prompts se content generate karoge, toh **har chapter ke baad ek kaam zaroor karna**.

Apni notebook utha lo, aur generated content ko padhte hue 5 ya 6 chhote bullet points likho jo bilkul aapke apne haath se hon. Yeh viva ke liye aapka cheat sheet ban jayega. Examiner jab puchega "iss chapter mein aapne kya kiya", toh aapko AI generated content yaad nahi karna padega. Aapko apne notes yaad karne padenge, jo chapter ke saath naturally align hote hain.

Yeh ek detail hai jo aapko safe rakhegi.

---

Toh ab aapke paas yeh poora setup ho gaya:

Ek master prompt jo overall rules define karta hai. Paanch chapter-specific sub-prompts (Introduction, Literature Review, Methodology, Results, Conclusion). Ek bonus abstract prompt.

Use kaise karenge: Pehle master prompt set karo, phir jis chapter ka content chahiye uska sub-prompt use karo. Dono ek saath model ko denge taaki dono level ke rules apply hon.

Kya aap chahte ho main ek **sample run** karke dikhau? Matlab ek dummy project leke (jaise "IoT based smart irrigation system" ya "CNN based diabetic retinopathy detection"), aur master prompt + Introduction sub-prompt use karke actual Chapter 1 likh ke dikhau? Isse aapko exact output style ka idea aa jayega aur aap dekh paoge ki yeh prompts kaisa content produce karenge.
